When you need to use the ID token, you can retrieve the token from the currently signed-in user like this:

```swift
import FirebaseAuth

if let user = Auth.auth().currentUser {
    user.getIDToken(completion: { (idToken, error) in
        if let error = error {
            print("Error getting ID token: \(error.localizedDescription)")
            return
        }

        if let idToken = idToken {
            // Use idToken here
            print("ID Token: \(idToken)")
        }
    })
}
```

The `getIDToken(completion:)` method retrieves the latest ID token from the current user, ensuring that you are dealing with an unexpired token. So you don't need to worry about storing and reusing the token within an hour before it expires.

